      "content": "I completely understand the drive to eliminate guesswork, but I must insist that a shift to strict, rigid rules could silently degrade the very accuracy these teams rely on for their most complex, high-stakes decisions. If we abandon the current engine before the migration completes, we risk losing the nuanced edge that makes our work so effective, and the new system might not be ready to handle that complexity. We need to pause the decommissioning process until we can validate that the new engine can actually replicate or surpass the nuanced capabilities of the old one without sacrificing performance.",
